  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I felt I really couldn't go anymore anyway.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's when my father said that he was a veteran, and I had a right to go to school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But it was not-- didn't help.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I remember one or two incidents when we, in the beginning, in '33, when the youth leader, his name was Baldur von Schirach, Hitler's youth leader-- came to town to talk to the students.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we all-- all the schools, I guess, from maybe high school on, from the the age of 9 or 10 on, had to march downtown to meet-- to listen to this leader, youth later, to him talk.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there was a real conflict because everybody had to use-- were supposed to used the Hitler salute, Heil Hitler.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then, some decree came out that Jewish children were not allowed to do the Hitler salute.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
